Yeah, I'll second that.<br>
<br>
I have a level 51 monk. I quit there and left in in  PoH for a year or so, because of the epidemic.<br>
<br>
Pulling really isn't that hard, especially with taggers. FD was probably actually harder before the 35+ nerf, simply because tagging hadn't been invented yet.<br>
<br>
And because monks used to be a niche. A pre-kunark monk wouldn't have his honor ruined by having someone tag off of him. He'd sit there all day til he got it right, and walk back with one mob.<br>
<br>
'Course, kunark rolls along, iksars are monks, then velious and it's insane for a monk to use fists, and monks are no longer the class described above.<br>
<br>
I would have LOVED to see content designed to challenge monks, I would have loved to see monks be a pulling class. But unfortunately, VI said they'd never balance the class around FD pulling, or something.<br>
<br>
I'd play my monk if FD pulling was the awe-inspiring feat that it was for me back in old CT prekunark, watching Jondoe Mongoose (they all fit mongoose in their name somewhere) finally succeed in splitting 10+ caster lizards by himself.<br>
<br>
