<br>
I have to laugh at this........<br>
<br>
16-22 Pulling 10-16 mob kites (hounds) in EK, pffft easy.<br>
<br>
22-30 Pulling EVERY aviak out of the aviak tree in SK(which is quite a sight, erm so I have been told), pffft easy.<br>
<br>
30-40 cougars, wolves etc in IC, who cares about adds, pffft easy.<br>
<br>
40-50 can't find a place where I can PULL enough mobs (only able to find 8 or so socials at a time), pffft been easy though.<br>
<br>
Get an add that runs at the wrong speed, mez it and keep kiting the rest. selo (w/o drum), aoe (with brass), pffft easy.  In case of a lag spike, your going to take a little dmg, so twist in heals no biggie.  <br>
<br>
The one thing I learned (and I learned it while I was trying to make a huge train for a ss), is that you can time it so that all mobs (even if they are different speeds) can be placed in Aoe range at the same time while keeping them all out of melee range.  It's all timing and I find timing easy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jayteebushwacker>Jaytee Bushwacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Summoner Da'FoH</span><br>  Posts: 1184<br> <font color=#333333>(11/1/02 3:26:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=397.topic&index=48>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Elementally, my dear Watson!</span><hr size=1> Why thank you for the compliment sir =) <p><hr>
